nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.experiment

Class Treatment<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.experiment.Treatment<A,R,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the absolute storage type for the simulation time, e.g. Calendar, Duration, or Double.
    R - the relative type for time storage, e.g. Long for the Calendar. For most non-calendar types, the absolute and relative types are the same.
    T - the extended type itself to be able to implement functions on the simulation time.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Treatment.CalendarDouble, Treatment.CalendarFloat, Treatment.CalendarLong, Treatment.TimeDouble, Treatment.TimeDoubleUnit, Treatment.TimeFloat, Treatment.TimeFloatUnit, Treatment.TimeLong

    public class Treatment<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The treatment is comprises the specification of input data, the runControl and the specification of output data. (Sol:1982, Oeren & Zeigler:1979)

                 R runLength,
                 ReplicationMode replicationMode)
        constructs a Treatment.
        Parameters:
        experiment - reflects the experiment
        id - an id to recognize the treatment
        startTime - the absolute start time of a run (can be zero)
        warmupPeriod - the relative warmup time of a run (can be zero), included in the runLength
        runLength - the run length of a run (relative to the start time)
        replicationMode - the replication mode of this treatment
